<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
Species characterised by pale, usually thinly epilithic thallus, rather large perithecia leaving shallow to deep pits in the rock, involucrellum usually covering more than half of the exciple, ascospores (21-)26-30(-34) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(9-)11-13(-14) mm, morphologically difficult to separate from 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. subdevergens" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="subdevergens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. subdevergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the sequence divergence in ITS 6.8-7.4%.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
