<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
The exciple wall of 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. kuusamoensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="kuusamoensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. kuusamoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is usually dark brown or black. However, one specimen with a pale exciple wall and one specimen with both pale and dark exciple walls have similar ITS sequences compared to the specimens with dark exciple walls. This species was erroneously reported as 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. subjunctiva" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="subjunctiva">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. subjunctiva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pykaelae, J" journalOrPublisher="Memoranda Societatis pro Fauna et Flora Fennica" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" pagination="34 - 42" refId="B36" refString="Pykaelae, J, 2010a. Notes on the lichen flora of Saana and Malla fells in northern Finland. Memoranda Societatis pro Fauna et Flora Fennica 86: 34 - 42" title="Notes on the lichen flora of Saana and Malla fells in northern Finland." volume="86" year="2010 a">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pykälä">Pykaelae</normalizedToken>
(2010a)
</bibRefCitation>
, while 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. subjunctiva" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="subjunctiva">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. subjunctiva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has larger spores and longer periphysoids. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nyl., Flora 55: 362" authorityYear="1872" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Verrucaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Verrucaria devergens" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="devergens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Verrucaria devergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a shorter involucrellum. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pykaelae, Kantelinen &amp; Myllys" authorityYear="2020" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Verrucaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Verrucaria kuusamoensis" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="kuusamoensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Verrucaria kuusamoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be most difficult to separate from 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. subdevergens" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="subdevergens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. subdevergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. difficilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="difficilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. difficilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These species show wide overlap in their morphology. 
